<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-03-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-03-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="803" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d803">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hill</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Merry</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-03-14"><hi rend="italic">March 14,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Hill states that a delay of thirty days to present proofs for the
                            arbitration of the Gelbtrunk claim in form requested by Salvador is
                            granted; that this action closes the agreement to arbitrate the claim,
                            and that proofs will accordingly be presented.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>